AB  - We extend the Quantum Transmitting Boundary Method (QTBM), a numerical algorithm for solving the two-dimensional SchrOdinger equation for scattering states, to include an applied magnetic field to 2D systems. We apply this technique to simulate the magneto-transport of a periodically corrugated electron channel. The conductance quantization of such structure is recovered when the channel is long. The index of this quantization is a non-monotonic function of energy.
