AB  - The impurity breakdown was simulated in numerical calculations. The distribution function for an electron in the electric field was calculated using the Monte-Carlo method. The electron concentration in the impurity ground state and in the first subband was determined by solving the rate equations. It was found out that a population inversion between the 1s-level and the bottom of the first subband is likely to arise. The requirements for the population inversion to occur were determined.
