AB  - A model for the coupling of the classical and quantum regions of a quantum well laser diode is presented. The calculation of carrier transport in different regions of the laser is first discussed. Then a discretization of the carrier continuity equations in and around the quantum well is presented in detail. The model is finally tested through the simulation of three different GaAs/AlGaAs lasers. The results are discussed, and the importance of carrier capture is demonstrated.
