AB  - The numerical discretization aspects of the quantum transport simulation of finite open systems are clarified in the framework of the discrete phase-space and lattice Weyl-Wigner formulation (LWWF) of quantum dynamics. For accurate numerical simulation of resonant tunneling devices at zero bias, the symmetry of closure and/or zero-current symmetry has to be imposed to avoid obtaining absurd results, particularly for asymmetric double-barrier structures at zero bias, where previous treatments were inadequate.
