AB  - Studying the transport characteristics of carriers in quantum dot (QD) film provides theory support for the structure design and performance improvement of QD film device. However, time of flight experiment can only test the global optoelectric current signal brought by the carrier transport, and cannot analyze the carrier transport in the transport layer. Here, the hopping transport model of photogenerated carriers in QD films was established to study the expansion and drift movement of carriers in the PDE module of COMSOL. According to the material properties of the actual QD films, the carrier transport in single-size QD films was studied.
