AB  - Using first-principle and semi-empirical methods, optical responses and transport characteristics of hybrid CNT-based diodes are studied. The junction is realized by a combination of doping of one half of a nanotube and applying a transverse electric field to the other. Calculations are carried out in the framework of the density functional theory and the nonequilibrium Green function method. The possibility of using these rectifiers in optical nanoantennas is discussed.
