AB  - Quantum efficiency is an important image sensor characteristic, connected to the wavelength-dependent signal collection and crosstalk. Simulation of quantum efficiency provides insight into the physical mechanisms within the pixel to guide development. We present a method of obtaining a numerical, physically-based photodiode model which can be used for faster predictions of QE, as well as provide graphical insight into the processes of crosstalk. Simulations are compared against experimental results for a 1.1µm BSI pixel.
